review_body: I love Google Earth! I use it to explore areas that I vacation in, before and after. It helps in deciding when and where I'm going to spend my time. And no more getting lost when following directions from locals..... Before Google Earth I was a map freak. I would plot literally every mile, every gas...Full ReviewI love Google Earth! I use it to explore areas that I vacation in, before and after. It helps in deciding when and where I'm going to spend my time. And no more getting lost when following directions from locals..... Before Google Earth I was a map freak. I would plot literally every mile, every gas stop, rest stop, etc. And I could predict my miles to travel by the markings on the map.

Google Earth is BY FAR my most frequently used app. I've been known to spend hours at a time on there. Between exploring "new world's" by soaring above like an eagle or zooming in and seeing my car in the driveway, or revisiting old haunts to see how they've changed, it more than maps. It often has ...Full ReviewGoogle Earth is BY FAR my most frequently used app. I've been known to spend hours at a time on there. Between exploring "new world's" by soaring above like an eagle or zooming in and seeing my car in the driveway, or revisiting old haunts to see how they've changed, it more than maps. It often has emotions and feelings attached. Then when I thought it couldn't get better...3D model excites a whole nother dimension...literally

OK AFTER MONTHS OF CRASHING, I FIGURED OUT FIX: 1) go into Google Earth's "App Info": 2) click, "FORCE STOP"; 3) click, "Storage" and BOTH "CLEAR CACHE" and "CLEAR STORAGE"; 4) click "Permissions" and make sure BOTH "Location" AND "Storage" are granted/on; 5) Exit 6) Restart Google Earth (it shouldn...Full ReviewOK AFTER MONTHS OF CRASHING, I FIGURED OUT FIX: 1) go into Google Earth's "App Info": 2) click, "FORCE STOP"; 3) click, "Storage" and BOTH "CLEAR CACHE" and "CLEAR STORAGE"; 4) click "Permissions" and make sure BOTH "Location" AND "Storage" are granted/on; 5) Exit 6) Restart Google Earth (it shouldn't crash) BUT go back in to "App Info" and check/set "Permissions" granted as shown above in step 4. IMPORTANT: UNINSTALL/RE-INSTALL/ UPDATE is NOT NECESSARY, AND IN FACT, WILL UNDO THE FIX.
